<doc>
  <member name="D2D1_THREADING_MODE">
    <summary>
      <para>Specifies the threading mode used while simultaneously creating the device, factory, and device context.</para>
    </summary>
    <seealso cref="D2D1_CREATION_PROPERTIES" />
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/Direct2D/multi-threaded-direct2d-apps">Multithreaded Direct2D Apps</seealso>
  </member>
  <member name="D2D1_THREADING_MODE.D2D1_THREADING_MODE_SINGLE_THREADED">
    <summary>
      <para>Resources may only be invoked serially.  Device context state is not protected from multi-threaded access.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D2D1_THREADING_MODE.D2D1_THREADING_MODE_MULTI_THREADED">
    <summary>
      <para>Resources may be invoked from multiple threads. Resources use interlocked reference counting and their state is protected.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D2D1_THREADING_MODE.D2D1_THREADING_MODE_FORCE_DWORD">
    <summary></summary>
  </member>
</doc>